headline: Can Cadence (CDNS) Maintain Its Innovation Edge Amid Evolving Trade Tensions and Supply Chain Risks?
summary: Cadence Design Systems recently presented at the OCP Global Summit 2025 at the San Jose Convention Center, where Ashutosh Mauskar, Vice President of Product Management, featured insights into custom systems design and analysis products. This appearance highlights Cadence's ongoing commitment to staying at the forefront of innovation within the open compute and custom silicon design ecosystem. headline: Alcor Micro to Showcase Latest Arm-based CPU Platform "Mobius100 (CSS V3)" at OCP Global Summit 2025
summary: Alcor Micro (8054.TWO), a subsidiary of Egis Technology Inc. (6462.TWO), will participate in the Open Compute Project (OCP) Global Summit 2025 held in San Jose, California, to showcase its latest Arm-based CPU platform — Mobius100 (CSS V3). The 8-core emulation platform is purpose-built for Artificial Intelligence (AI) and High-Performance Computing (HPC) servers, demonstrating Alcor Micro's leadership in open computing innovation and advanced chip architecture.
